 :tx/rationale "ATT-2 ARCHITECTURE DECISION: DUAL-PATH STATE MODEL. The presentation counter problem has two fundamentally different requirements that demand different persistence strategies. REQUIREMENT 1 (HOT PATH): On every status call, read and update presentation counts per block label. Must be fast (<1ms), must not change the read-only contract of status, must not add store write overhead. REQUIREMENT 2 (COLD PATH): Hebbian boosts and Bayesian learned weights are KNOWLEDGE — they persist across sessions, are queryable, participate in harvest, and calibrate over time. SOLUTION: Two persistence paths. Hot path: .braid/cache/attention.json — a session-scoped JSON file containing {session_id: String, counts: HashMap<String, usize>, last_command: String, omitted_labels: Vec<String>}. Reset when session_id changes. Fast read/write, no store involvement. Cold path: datoms on attention entities (:attention/hebbian-boost, :attention/learned-weight, :attention/calibration-count). Written only when learning signals fire (verbose-request, task close). Queryable, harvestable, durable. The cache FEEDS the learning loop but is not part of it. Same pattern as .braid/cache/fitness.json and .braid/cache/coherence.json (PERF-2)."
